## 4. Required Headers Reference

Every request to `na.business-api.amazon.com` requires these headers:

| Header | Value | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| `x-amz-access-token` | LWA access_token | Required on ALL calls |
| `x-amz-user-email` | org account email | Required on Product Search & Order Details |
| `x-amz-date` | `YYYYMMDDTHHmmssZ` | UTC timestamp |
| `Content-Type` | `application/json` | Required on POST requests |
| `user-agent` | `KCSProcurement/1.0 (Language=GAS;Platform=Google)` | Helps Amazon diagnose issues |

```javascript
/**
 * Builds standard headers for all Amazon Business API requests.
 * @param {boolean} includeUserEmail - include x-amz-user-email header
 * @returns {Object} headers object
 */
function buildHeaders(includeUserEmail = true) {
  const headers = {
    'x-amz-access-token': getAccessToken(),
    'x-amz-date': getAmzDate(),
    'user-agent': 'KCSProcurement/1.0 (Language=GAS;Platform=Google)',
    'Content-Type': 'application/json'
  };
  if (includeUserEmail) {
    headers['x-amz-user-email'] = getProp('AMZ_USER_EMAIL');
  }
  return headers;
}

/**
 * Returns current UTC time in Amazon-required format: YYYYMMDDTHHmmssZ
 */
function getAmzDate() {
  const now = new Date();
  return now.toISOString().replace(/[-:]/g, '').replace(/\.\d{3}/, '');
}
```

