## 5. Product Search API — Price Catalog Verification

**Base URL:** `https://na.business-api.amazon.com`  
**API Version:** `2020-08-26`  
**Rate Limit:** 0.5 req/sec, burst 10  
**Purpose:** Verify the teacher's submitted price against the live Amazon catalog price before committing to any order.

### 5.1 Get Product & Price by ASIN (Primary Method)

Use this when the teacher's request contains an ASIN (e.g., extracted from an Amazon URL).

```
GET /products/2020-08-26/products/{asin}
  ?productRegion=US
  &locale=en_US
  &shippingPostalCode=33710
  &quantity={qty}
  &facets=OFFERS
```

```javascript
/**
 * Fetches live product data and offer price for a single ASIN.
 * @param {string} asin - Amazon Standard Item Number
 * @param {number} quantity - quantity intended to purchase (affects quantity pricing)
 * @returns {Object} parsed product result or throws on error
 */
function getProductByAsin(asin, quantity) {
  quantity = quantity || 1;
  const postal = getProp('KCS_SHIPPING_POSTAL') || '33710';
  
  const url = `https://na.business-api.amazon.com/products/2020-08-26/products/${asin}` +
    `?productRegion=US&locale=en_US&shippingPostalCode=${postal}` +
    `&quantity=${quantity}&facets=OFFERS`;

  const response = UrlFetchApp.fetch(url, {
    method: 'GET',
    headers: buildHeaders(true),
    muteHttpExceptions: true
  });

  const code = response.getResponseCode();
  const body = JSON.parse(response.getContentText());

  if (code === 200) return body;

  // Structured error handling
  throw new ApiError('ProductSearch', code, body);
}
```

### 5.2 Search by Keyword (Fallback — when no ASIN available)

Use this if the teacher only provides a product name or URL without an ASIN.

```
GET /products/2020-08-26/products
  ?productRegion=US
  &locale=en_US
  &keywords={encoded_keywords}
  &shippingPostalCode=33710
  &availability=InStockOnly
  &pageSize=5
  &facets=OFFERS
```

```javascript
/**
 * Searches for products by keyword. Returns top 5 results for review.
 * @param {string} keywords - search terms
 * @returns {Object} SearchProductsResult
 */
function searchProductsByKeyword(keywords) {
  const postal = getProp('KCS_SHIPPING_POSTAL') || '33710';
  
  const url = `https://na.business-api.amazon.com/products/2020-08-26/products` +
    `?productRegion=US&locale=en_US` +
    `&keywords=${encodeURIComponent(keywords)}` +
    `&shippingPostalCode=${postal}` +
    `&availability=InStockOnly` +
    `&pageSize=5&facets=OFFERS`;

  const response = UrlFetchApp.fetch(url, {
    method: 'GET',
    headers: buildHeaders(true),
    muteHttpExceptions: true
  });

  const code = response.getResponseCode();
  const body = JSON.parse(response.getContentText());

  if (code === 200) return body;
  throw new ApiError('ProductSearch', code, body);
}
```

### 5.3 Batch Lookup by ASIN List (up to 30 ASINs)

Useful for reconciliation or bulk verification passes.

```
POST /products/2020-08-26/products/getProductsByAsins
Content-Type: application/json
```

**Request body:**
```json
{
  "productIds": ["B08N5WRWNW", "B07XJ8C8F5"],
  "productRegion": "US",
  "locale": "en_US",
  "shippingPostalCode": "33710",
  "quantity": 1,
  "facets": ["OFFERS"]
}
```

```javascript
/**
 * Fetches price data for multiple ASINs in one call.
 * @param {string[]} asinList - array of ASINs, max 30
 * @returns {Object} { matchingProductCount, products[], notFoundAsins[] }
 */
function getProductsByAsinBatch(asinList) {
  if (asinList.length > 30) throw new Error('Batch limit is 30 ASINs per call');

  const body = {
    productIds: asinList,
    productRegion: 'US',
    locale: 'en_US',
    shippingPostalCode: getProp('KCS_SHIPPING_POSTAL') || '33710',
    quantity: 1,
    facets: ['OFFERS']
  };

  const response = UrlFetchApp.fetch(
    'https://na.business-api.amazon.com/products/2020-08-26/products/getProductsByAsins',
    {
      method: 'POST',
      headers: buildHeaders(true),
      payload: JSON.stringify(body),
      muteHttpExceptions: true
    }
  );

  const code = response.getResponseCode();
  const parsed = JSON.parse(response.getContentText());
  if (code === 200) return parsed;
  throw new ApiError('ProductSearch/Batch', code, parsed);
}
```

### 5.4 Parse Price from Product Response

This is the critical extraction step — pulls the featured offer price out of the API response.

```javascript
/**
 * Extracts the best available offer price and offerId from a ProductsResult.
 * The first offer in OFFERS facet is always the featured/best offer.
 *
 * @param {Object} productResult - single product from API response
 * @returns {Object|null} { offerId, asin, title, amount, currencyCode, formattedPrice, taxExclusiveAmount, available }
 */
function extractBestOffer(productResult) {
  const offers = productResult?.includedDataTypes?.OFFERS;
  if (!offers || offers.length === 0) return null;

  // First offer = featured offer (Amazon's recommended buying option)
  const offer = offers;

  return {
    offerId: offer.offerId,
    asin: productResult.asin,
    title: productResult.title,
    // Primary price (what customer pays, may include tax)
    amount: offer.price?.value?.amount,
    currencyCode: offer.price?.value?.currencyCode || 'USD',
    formattedPrice: offer.price?.formattedPrice,
    // Tax-exclusive price (use for budget comparison)
    taxExclusiveAmount: offer.taxExclusivePrice?.taxExclusiveAmount?.amount,
    // Availability string e.g. "In Stock"
    available: offer.availability,
    // Merchant info for audit trail
    merchantName: offer.merchant?.name,
    merchantId: offer.merchant?.merchantId,
    // Quantity limits (min/max purchasable)
    minQty: offer.quantityLimits?.minQuantity,
    maxQty: offer.quantityLimits?.maxQuantity
